\begin_layout Section
Collaborations
\end_layout

\begin_layout Labeling
\labelwidthstring 00.00.0000
\begin_inset Formula $\mathbf{Imeka}$
\end_inset

 Intership with Imeka Solutions Inc.; a company specialized in brain imaging
 specifically white matter, neuroinflammation, free-water and more.
 We will develop mechanisms and modify others already in place to integrate
 the MRDS-based pipeline into the Imeka's software infrastructure.
 This could enable the ability to test the pipeline on large public and
 clinical Imeka databases with more than 
\begin_inset Formula $5,000$
\end_inset

 MRI exams (Duration: 3-6 months).
\end_layout

\begin_layout Labeling
\labelwidthstring 00.00.0000
\begin_inset Formula $\mathbf{NYU}$
\end_inset

 Possible collaboration with the NYU MRI Biophysics Group, which is one
 of the most relevant laboratories in the field.
 It will focus on multimetric analysis of white matter tracts in the multi-compa
rtment standard model (Duration: 3-6 months).
\end_layout

\begin_layout Labeling
\labelwidthstring 00.00.0000
\begin_inset Formula $\mathbf{UMC}$
\end_inset

 Possible collaboration with Chen-Pei Lin applying the proposed pipeline
 to HARDI multi-shell post mortem Parkinson brain data.
\end_layout

